KANO – Nasiru Ali Ahmad, a ranking member of the House of Representatives on Friday evening won the All Progressive Congress ticket for Nasarawa federal constituency in Kano. Ahmad was affirmed by 53 out of 55 delegates that converged at Hisba Office, Nasarawa local government secretariat for the exercise. The exercise was presided over by Jamilu Sani Rano, a State APC observer, INEC officials, DSS, Police and other Security Agencies. -Advertisement- Mr Rano said 55 Delegates participated in the exercise, while 53 cast their vote in favour of Hon. Nasiru Ali Ahmad. Ahmad overwhelming victory was sequel to the withdrawal of Lamin Sani, a former chairman, Nasarawa local government from the race over personal reasons. In his acceptance, Nasiru Ali Ahmad, said “Allah gives power to whom he so wishes”, adding that there was no rivalry between him and Lamin Sani because they are brothers. Ahmad assured that, he would continue to influence dividends of democracy to the constituency if reelected to the Green chamber again by the end of the 2023 General election.